import subprocess
import os

repo_path = "/home/gem/repo_31777fbb-fb66-4af6-9847-d6b2c9f530e1"

# Read the GitHub token from gh config file
print("=== Reading GitHub token from gh config ===")
gh_config_path = os.path.expanduser('~/.config/gh/hosts.yml')

with open(gh_config_path, 'r') as f:
    content = f.read()
    token = None
    for line in content.split('\n'):
        if 'oauth_token:' in line:
            token = line.split('oauth_token:')[1].strip()
            break

if not token:
    print("❌ Could not find token in gh config")
else:
    print("✅ Token found")
    
    # Get current remote URL
    result = subprocess.run(['git', 'remote', 'get-url', 'origin'], capture_output=True, text=True)
    current_url = result.stdout.strip()
    print(f"\nCurrent remote URL: {current_url}")
    
    # Extract repo from current URL
    if 'github.com' in current_url:
        # Extract owner/repo from URL
        if current_url.startswith('https://'):
            repo_path_part = current_url.split('github.com/')[-1].replace('.git', '')
        else:
            repo_path_part = current_url.split(':')[-1].replace('.git', '')
        
        print(f"Repository: {repo_path_part}")
        
        # Update git remote to use token directly
        new_url = f"https://x-access-token:{token}@github.com/{repo_path_part}.git"
        print(f"\n=== Updating remote URL ===")
        result = subprocess.run(['git', 'remote', 'set-url', 'origin', new_url], capture_output=True, text=True)
        
        if result.returncode == 0:
            print("✅ Remote URL updated successfully")
        else:
            print(f"❌ Failed to update remote: {result.stderr}")

# Create PR using GitHub CLI
pr_title = "Refactor: Replace textarea with Monaco Editor for JSON editing"
pr_body = """## Summary
Refactored the JSON Merger application to use Monaco Editor instead of plain textarea elements for a professional code editing experience.

## Changes Made
- ✅ Installed `@monaco-editor/react` package
- ✅ Replaced plain `<textarea>` elements with Monaco Editor components
- ✅ Added JSON syntax highlighting with proper color coding
- ✅ Implemented line numbers and professional dark theme
- ✅ Added format-on-paste and format-on-type features
- ✅ Improved UI/UX with better styling and layout
- ✅ Enhanced CSS with custom styles for editor wrappers and merged result display
- ✅ Updated button labels with emojis for better user experience
- ✅ Added example JSON data in initial state

## Features
- **Monaco Editor Integration**: Professional VS Code-style editor for JSON editing
- **Syntax Highlighting**: Proper JSON syntax highlighting with color coding
- **Line Numbers**: Easy reference with visible line numbers
- **Dark Theme**: Professional dark theme matching modern code editors
- **Auto-formatting**: Format on paste and type for better code quality
- **Multiple Editors**: Support for adding/removing multiple JSON editors
- **Real-time Merging**: Live preview of merged JSON output

## Testing
✅ Tested in browser - application works correctly
✅ All features functional (add/delete/reset editors)
✅ Monaco Editor rendering properly with syntax highlighting
✅ JSON merging works as expected

## Screenshots
See the working application with Monaco Editor successfully integrated and functioning.
"""

print("=== Creating Pull Request ===")
result = subprocess.run(
    ['gh', 'pr', 'create', 
     '--title', pr_title,
     '--body', pr_body,
     '--base', 'master',
     '--head', branch_name],
    capture_output=True,
    text=True,
    timeout=30
)

print("STDOUT:", result.stdout)
if result.stderr:
    print("STDERR:", result.stderr)
print("Return code:", result.returncode)

if result.returncode == 0:
    print("\n✅ Pull request created successfully!")
else:
    print("\n⚠️ PR creation had issues")
